UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304387882900074
AB  - The effects of discrimination in favor of metropolitan direct investment in colonies on the size and composition of foreign investment there and the profits accruing therefrom have been derived with the help of a simple model. Empirical studies show that the rate of return to U.K. investment in her colonies was significantly higher than in non-British LDCs, although some doubt remains as to the extent to which this result is explained by data imperfections.
ER  - 
